## {{ rule.title }}

{% set out = rule.outputs[0].value | from_json -%}
{% if rule.language == "de" -%}
[DBA-USA Art. 10](https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-trty/germtech.pdf) deckelt die deutsche Quellensteuer auf U.S.-Aktiendividenden auf 15 %; [DBA-USA Art. 23](https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-trty/germtech.pdf) (Methodenartikel) verlangt, dass Deutschland als Wohnsitzstaat die anteilige U.S.-Steuer anrechnet. Diese Anrechnung **muss** über [§ 32d Abs. 5 EStG](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__32d.html) laufen — eine eigenständige "Treaty-Anrechnung" außerhalb der [§ 32d](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__32d.html)-Logik fällt **fail-closed** aus, weil sie die Pro-Item-Caps unterläuft.

Für 2025:

- Treaty-Anrechnung (muss 0 sein, sonst fail-closed): **{{ out.treaty_credit_eur | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- Kapitalertragsteuer **vor** Treaty-Prüfung: **{{ out.income_tax_before_treaty | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- Kapitalertragsteuer **nach** Treaty-Prüfung: **{{ out.income_tax_after_treaty | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- SolZ vor Treaty: **{{ out.solidarity_surcharge_before_treaty | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- SolZ nach Treaty: **{{ out.solidarity_surcharge_after_treaty | money(currency="EUR") }}**

Pro-Posten Treaty-Dividenden-Items (für die Cross-Border-Spur in TREATY25-17):

{% for item in out.treaty_dividend_packet_items -%}
- {{ item.item_id }} ({{ item.dividend_class }}, owner={{ item.owner_slot }}): brutto **{{ item.gross_dividend_eur | money(currency="EUR") }}**, deutsche Vorsteuer **{{ item.germany_precredit_tax_eur | money(currency="EUR") }}**, deutsche Anrechnung U.S.-Steuer **{{ item.germany_residence_credit_eur | money(currency="EUR") }}**, Art. 10-Deckel **{{ item.article_10_source_tax_ceiling_eur | money(currency="EUR") }}**
{% endfor %}
{% else -%}
[DBA-USA Article 10](https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-trty/germtech.pdf) caps Germany's withholding on U.S. equity dividends at 15 %; [DBA-USA Article 23](https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-trty/germtech.pdf) (the methods article) requires Germany as residence state to credit the proportional U.S. tax. That credit **must** flow through [§ 32d Abs. 5 EStG](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__32d.html) — a freestanding "treaty credit" outside the [§ 32d](https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/estg/__32d.html) logic **fails closed**, because it would bypass the per-item caps.

For 2025:

- Treaty credit (must be zero, otherwise fail-closed): **{{ out.treaty_credit_eur | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- Capital tax **before** treaty check: **{{ out.income_tax_before_treaty | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- Capital tax **after** treaty check: **{{ out.income_tax_after_treaty | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- SolZ before treaty: **{{ out.solidarity_surcharge_before_treaty | money(currency="EUR") }}**
- SolZ after treaty: **{{ out.solidarity_surcharge_after_treaty | money(currency="EUR") }}**

Per-item treaty dividend packet (handed to the cross-border treaty graph at TREATY25-17):

{% for item in out.treaty_dividend_packet_items -%}
- {{ item.item_id }} ({{ item.dividend_class }}, owner={{ item.owner_slot }}): gross **{{ item.gross_dividend_eur | money(currency="EUR") }}**, German pre-credit tax **{{ item.germany_precredit_tax_eur | money(currency="EUR") }}**, German credit for U.S. tax **{{ item.germany_residence_credit_eur | money(currency="EUR") }}**, Article 10 source ceiling **{{ item.article_10_source_tax_ceiling_eur | money(currency="EUR") }}**
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

